Summary

Experienced Linux magician, workaholic, and a perfectionist with a passion for technology.

I engineer, implement and maintain resilient highly available infrastructures (cloud and on-premise) using open-source tools and the very best of practices.

HashiCorp and Grafana Labs fanboy ♥ I'm also a Gentooman and a proud owner of a homelab of 4 Gentoo boxes managed by Ansible.

I'm looking to become a better programmer and feel genuinely excited about the possibility of writing in Golang or/and Rust in my work time.

Experience

Cinarra

15/05/2019 - Present

DevOps/SRE

Big Data analytics for the third biggest telecom provider in Japan (location based advertisement).

Antiquated infrastructure refactoring in the cloud (AWS) and in an on-premise environment (~100 very beefy hosts) with no direct access.

I've joined Cinarra as a junior DevOps and snowballed into a Super Start in 3 years, thanks to the incredible, talented Cinarra folks and unique challenges SoftBank provided.

I gave back. Cinarra gained a modern, scalable, highly available and resilient infrastructure with best in class monitoring, configuration in code and automatic deployments.

During my time in Cinarra, I've implemented:

  • Infrastructure as a code using Ansible, Packer, Nomad and Terraform
  • Containerization - transformation from legacy infrastructure with zero container usage to full containerization
  • Service discovery, DNS load-balancing and a Service Mesh with Consul
  • Observability with VictoriaMetrics and Grafana Loki - metrics and logs in one place with almost zero operational costs
  • CI/CD with GitHub Actions using self-hosted workers
  • Secret management, short lived unique credentials, policy based access and painless mTLS with Vault
  • Personal PR based DEV environment that everyone can use
